# Scheduled Pipeliens

##    Jenkins Pipeiine - Scheduled Build
you will learn how to **schedule a Jenkins pipeline using cron**.

pipeline {
    agent any 
    environment {
        INSTITUTE_NAME = "Pathnex"
    }
    triggers {
        cron('H 2 * * *')
    }
    stages {
        stage('Checkout') {
            steos {
                git url: 'https://github.com/pathnex/sample-java-pp.git''
            }
        }
        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn clean pacckage'
            }
        }
    }
}

